  "upgrade_suggestion": "2020 US Deluxe Edition 2LP 180g is the most comprehensive vinyl issue of this album (17 tracks vs. the original 2015 12-track LP). No meaningful sonic upgrade exists for this title on vinyl; the 2020 cut is the current canonical pressing.",
  "commentary": "Released March 27, 2015 by Centricity Music, *How Can It Be* is Lauren Daigle's debut studio album — the record that established her as a major contemporary Christian voice before *Look Up Child* broke her into mainstream pop visibility three years later. *First* (the lead single) and the title track *How Can It Be* both went to #1 on Billboard's Hot Christian Songs chart, with the album itself certified 2× Platinum by the RIAA.\n\nThe album was produced by Paul Mabury (who would also produce *Look Up Child*), with Jason Ingram contributing as co-writer on multiple tracks. Recorded in Nashville, the production sits in adult-contemporary worship territory — piano-and-strings ballads, mid-tempo pop-rock, Daigle's voice (often compared to Adele's) consistently the centerpiece. *How Can It Be* won Best Contemporary Christian Music Album at the 2017 Grammys — Daigle's first Grammy, before her *Look Up Child* repeat in 2019.\n\nThe original 2015 release was 12 tracks. Centricity reissued the album as a *Deluxe Edition* in late 2015 / early 2016 with 5 additional tracks: live versions, an alternate mix, and a previously-unreleased song. The 2016 deluxe was the version that anchored the album's continued chart presence through 2017–2018.\n\n**About this 2020 US Deluxe Edition pressing (2×LP, 180g, gatefold):** Centricity Music issued the deluxe configuration on vinyl in 2020 (catno `9619210101`), five years after the original digital release. 17 tracks across four sides at standard 33⅓ RPM, on **180g** vinyl with a full-color gatefold jacket and custom die-cut inner sleeves. The vinyl format choice (33⅓ rather than the 45 RPM cut Centricity used for the *Look Up Child* LP) is appropriate to the longer total runtime — 17 tracks at 45 RPM would have required 3 LPs.\n\nThis is the more comprehensive vinyl edition of *How Can It Be* available — the original 12-track album was issued on standard-weight vinyl in 2015 (catno harder to find), while this 2020 deluxe is the canonical \"complete\" vinyl release.\n\n### Gemini Notes\n\nReleased in 2015, *How Can It Be* is the debut studio album by contemporary Christian music artist Lauren Daigle. The album was a massive commercial and critical success, winning a Billboard Music Award and earning a Grammy nomination. Its soulful pop sensibilities and Daigle's powerful, smoky vocals drew comparisons to Adele, bridging the gap between CCM and mainstream pop.\n\n**About this pressing:**",
